1. Introduction
1.1 Purpose
This Software Requirements Specification (SRS) document details the functional and non-functional requirements for ChopNow, a digital platform aimed at reducing food waste and improving access to affordable meals across Africa. This document serves as a foundational guide for the development team, stakeholders, and testers, ensuring a shared understanding of the system's objectives and functionalities. The scope of this SRS covers the entire ChopNow platform, encompassing both vendor and consumer-facing applications, as well as the backend infrastructure.
1.2 Document Conventions
This document adheres to the following conventions: * Bold text is used for emphasis and to highlight key terms. * Italic text is used for titles of documents or external references. * Code font is used for technical terms, code snippets, or specific UI elements. * Requirements are structured with unique identifiers (e.g., FR1, NFR1) for
traceability. * All diagrams are presented using standard UML notation where applicable.
1.3 Intended Audience and Reading Suggestions
This SRS is intended for a diverse audience, including: * Developers: To understand the system's requirements for design and implementation. * Project Managers: To monitor project scope, progress, and resource allocation. * Quality Assurance (QA) Testers: To develop test plans and validate system functionality. * Stakeholders/Business Analysts: To ensure the system aligns with business objectives and user needs. * Technical Writers: To develop user manuals and other documentation.
It is suggested that readers begin with the Introduction for an overview, proceed to the Overall Description for context, then delve into the detailed Functional and Non-functional Requirements. Sections on External Interface Requirements and System Features provide technical specifics, while the Appendices offer supplementary information.
1.4 Product Scope
ChopNow is a mobile-first digital platform designed to connect local food vendors with surplus food to consumers seeking affordable meals. The primary goal is to mitigate food waste and combat food insecurity in African urban centers. The platform will feature vendor registration, meal listing, discounted pricing, real-time notifications, secure payment processing, and order management. It will initially target key cities in Sub-Saharan Africa, with a focus on scalability and adaptability to diverse local contexts. The platform's success will be measured by reductions in food waste, increased access to affordable food, and improved economic opportunities for vendors.
